						<summary>

						<p>On the West and South walls of the central shrine, Nāgēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Year 5: 976 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Damaged and incomplete. It seems to record the distribution of the sheep which had been presented to the temple of Tirukkīḻkōṭṭattu-paramasvāmi at Tirukkuḍamukkil in Pāmbūr-nāḍu, among several shepherds, for the supply of the necessary ghee by them for burning perpetual lamps in the temple.</p>						

						<p>Published in <hi rend="italic">S.I.I.,</hi> Vol. XIX No. 132. </p>						

						</summary>
